last_episode_to_air.name: Souvlaki
last_episode_to_air.overview: It's the end of an era as Josh, Tom and Ella move out of their share house and find that domestic bliss is hard to come by. Josh confronts Claire and weighs up whether a pasta maker or a therapist will best solve his problems.

name: Please Like Me
overview: After breaking up with his girlfriend, Josh comes to the realization that he is homosexual. With the support of his now ex girlfriend Claire, and his best friend and house mate Tom, Josh must help his mother with her battle with depression and the rest of his family embrace his new found lifestyle.

seasons.name: Season 1
seasons.overview: The first season begins with Josh realizing that he is gay after being dumped by his girlfriend and forced to move back home with his mother after she overdoses on painkillers.

seasons.name: Season 2
seasons.overview: The second season is set an unspecified number of years after the first season, and quite a few things have changed. Josh and Thomas now live with a cute new roommate, Patrick, Claire is in Germany, Josh is no longer an only child, and Mum is admitted to a psychiatric hospital. Somewhere in the middle of it all, Josh meets Arnold.

episodes.name: Rhubarb and Custard
episodes.overview: Josh's world is thrown into chaos after being dumped by his girlfriend, meeting a very good looking man, and having to care for his fragile mother.

episodes.name: Portuguese Custard Tarts
episodes.overview: Josh is off to church after God-fearing Aunty Peg catches him making out, and things are hotting up between best friend Tom and ex-girlfriend Claire.

episodes.name: Milk
episodes.overview: Josh attempts babysitting his new sister and charming his new housemate. As his house fills with semi-clothed twentysomethings and drunk, wary parents, Mum arrives with a sobering surprise.

episodes.name: Ham
episodes.overview: Tom meets a cute girl, Josh meets an odd boy, and a beer pong game gets really weird at a party. Mum is admitted to a psych hospital; Josh meets her fellow patients and feels strangely at home.

episodes.name: Parmigiana
episodes.overview: Geoffrey calls Josh and they go on a date; Arnold books himself into the same mental home as Mum; Dad and Mae have their first baby panic moment; Jenny discovers Tom is still having sex with Niamh.

episodes.name: Gang Keow Wan
episodes.overview: Claire declares she's coming home; Niamh finds out about Jenny; Patrick and Josh get stuck in a traffic jam; Patrick kisses Josh; Tom presents Jenny with a baby rabbit; Mum is distraught to discover that Stuart has a wife.

episodes.name: Sausage Sizzle
episodes.overview: Claire stays with Tom, Josh and Patrick; Josh asks Dad for money to pay the plumber; a cleaner catches Josh graffitiing a toilet wall; Mum and Ginger have a fight; the housemates go to see Jenny in a school production.

episodes.name: Lapin A La Cocotte
episodes.overview: Patrick tells Josh he's not sexually interested in him; Josh agrees to take Mum and her friends to the zoo; Tom and Jenny have a weird rabbit funeral and break up; Arnold kisses Josh.

episodes.name: Scroggin
episodes.overview: Mum and Josh go hiking in scenic remote Tasmania; Mum gets trapped in a waterhole by a snake.

episodes.name: Truffled Mac and Cheese
episodes.overview: Patrick moves out of the house; Tom eats all of Josh's special truffled mac and cheese.

episodes.name: Skinny Latte
episodes.overview: Josh's first day on the job at his coffee cart; Stuart tells Mum he's leaving.

episodes.name: Margherita
episodes.overview: Josh and Arnold go out dancing and bump into a very out-of-it Patrick; Arnold has an anxiety attack.

episodes.name: Eggplant
episodes.overview: Josh is surprised to find he's living in a romcom; Josh till can't seem to win Arnold over.

episodes.name: Simple Carbohydrates
episodes.overview: Josh, Tom, Arnold and Claire discuss Arnold's plan to come out to his parents at his birthday party; Mae and Dad have their biggest fight yet; Mum and Hannah have a big night out.

episodes.name: Croquembouche
episodes.overview: Josh, Tom and Hannah finally get to meet Arnold's parents; Arnold makes his big coming out announcement.

episodes.name: Natural Spring Water
episodes.overview: Josh, Tom and Arnold have a night to remember as they experiment with drugs, head to a nightclub, meet the intriguing Ella and end up spending a surprising night in hospital.

episodes.name: Coq Au Vin
episodes.overview: As the boys recover from their big night, Claire arrives home from Berlin; Josh finally admits that his pet chicken is a rooster.

episodes.overview: Tom and Ella make a nervous trip to the dentist; Josh and Claire have to deal with a decision that makes them realize they're growing up fast; Mum plots revenge when she learns Stuart is still seeing his wife.

episodes.name: Puff Pastry Pizza
episodes.overview: While Arnold is away at a maths summit, Josh takes advantage of his new open relationship status by hooking up with a stranger; Tom challenges Josh and Claire to smash his piÃ±ata.

episodes.name: Amoxicillin
episodes.overview: Josh agrees to visit Ben in hospital before his brain surgery, but keeps it a secret from Arnold; Tom discovers he has chlamydia and goes to ridiculous lengths to try and treat Ella without losing her.

episodes.name: Champagne
episodes.overview: As Josh waits to hear if Ben survives his surgery, Josh, Tom, Claire, Ella and Arnold find themselves stuck in the cabin of a giant observation wheel.

episodes.name: Christmas Trifle
episodes.overview: Christmas orphans Tom, Arnold, Ella, Claire and Hannah crowd around the table with Josh's family for a festive lunch.

episodes.name: Babaganoush
episodes.overview: A threesome goes wrong, teddy bears' lives are threatened, a lovers' tiff makes a family barbecue awkward, and a revelation over a chocolate quinoa slice makes Josh realize he's had it up to here with things.

episodes.name: Porridge
episodes.overview: A camping trip to celebrate Hannah's birthday goes pear-shaped. Josh and his friends face stormy weather, dampened spirits, a treasure hunt, a dead body and fireworks - both in the sky and in their tent.

episodes.name: Beluga Caviar
episodes.overview: Josh is single and ready to mingle, but a string of dating disasters has him wondering if it's all worth it. Meanwhile, Hannah has taken up boxing, while Mum seems to have taken up fighting - with anyone about anything.

episodes.name: Degustation
episodes.overview: Josh takes his divorced Mum and Dad to a cutting edge degustation dinner. As they work their way through fifteen delicious and intimidating courses, wine is consumed, emotions run high and secrets are spilled.

episodes.name: Burrito Bowl
episodes.overview: Josh reconnects with his first boyfriend, Geoffrey, who shows Josh some surprising new tricks. As Dad gets excited about a low-carb diet, Ella has a health scare. She encounters an extremely hot doctor making Tom jealous.
